SIMPLE: caucasian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Caucasian
<hw>Cau*ca"sian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the Caucasus, a mountainous region between the Black and
Caspian seas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the white races of mankind, of
whom the people about Mount Caucasus were formerly taken as the
type.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caucasian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Caucasian
<hw>Cau*ca"sian</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native or
inhabitant of the Caucasus, esp. a Circassian or Georgian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A member of any of the white races of
mankind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caucus</ent>⟦br⟧
